Proud Elder of <A HREF="http://24.19.82.195/~orbis/">Orbis Honesti</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufyleow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fyleow</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/00 6:51:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What level are you, when you attend a Plane raid?</span><hr size=1> Its different when the raiding party is level 46-51/52 than lvl 53+.  Fear raid can be considered harder to Hate raid but it all come down to team work and leadership (if everyone listens).  I have been going to fear raid and hate raid break-ins (pre-Kunark) with no deaths for quite some time.<br>
<br>
If you are of the higher level, its way easier.  2 or even 3 groups of level 55+ can break Fear without deaths.  Most of the time you don't need to fight in fear until you reach the &quot;safe&quot; corner.<br>
<br>
Greater Vocerations are very close to the level of mobs in Planes so Fire, Water, Air can nuke the mobs without problem.  GV Air can stun Inny after the debuffs had landed.<br>
<br>
If you run up to the wall in Hate, it can be considered &quot;safe&quot;, i have tried walking around up there (invis) and have mobs right below me wandering.  But its not a valid spot to strategize your army, imagine all of the raiding party sitting up to the top and come down for combat; its abit messy to my liking.  There is also the problem that you might aggro the mobs on the second floor.  I have had friends being summoned up top because of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzantenvaliturus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanten Valiturus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(9/26/00 6:52:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What level are you, when you attend a Plane raid?</span><hr size=1> There is a NEAR safe spot that most other servers don't take advantage of.  There are 3 static spawns when you zone in. These spawns, once killed will not respawn for 14 hours.  So if you zone in, kill them off, the gate house is a safe spot for many hours.<br>
<br>
The mobs are:<br>
Spite golem<br>
Cleric of Innoruuk<br>
Ire Ghast<br>
<br>
Kill those and you can stand in the middle of the room for hours and hours.<br>
<br>
My thoughts of fear or hate and the use of pets.  Do not be in a hurry to use pets.  Wait a couple trips before using them, get a feel for the planes before trying to control your pet.  When you do feel confident to use a pet, only summon him if you have NO lag, if you are experiencing any latency, you could have a real problem fast.  Once you have decided it's time, go to GREAT lengths to make sure you control your pet.  It could tarnish the reputation of all pet users in the planes. <p><TABLE>
